name: Missing You Netflix
summary: Netflix's latest release, "Missing You," is a captivating Harlan Coben thriller that has garnered mixed reactions. The series, inspired by John Waite's hit song, features a gripping first five minutes. Despite its intriguing premise, some critics argue that it fails to maintain momentum, leaving viewers with an unsatisfying and forgettable experience. Its convoluted plot, though initially impressive and head-spinning, ultimately becomes a hindrance, leading to an unsatisfying conclusion. However, other reviews praise the series as a worthy binge-watch for the new year, highlighting its effective use of dating apps as a central plot device. Overall, "Missing You" has divided critics, leaving viewers to determine whether its twists and turns deliver the thrilling experience they crave or merely leave them underwhelmed.

name: Amber Alert
summary: Several Amber Alerts were issued this weekend due to child abductions. In Olympia, Washington, two children were allegedly abducted and an Amber Alert was issued on Saturday. Fortunately, the children were found safe, and a suspect was arrested. In Knoxville, Tennessee, an Amber Alert was issued on Sunday for a two-year-old boy. The boy was eventually found safe. Another Amber Alert was issued for a 14-year-old girl in Los Angeles, California. She was located by authorities and the Amber Alert was canceled. In Portland, Oregon, two young sisters were found safe after an Amber Alert was issued. Their father was detained. An Amber Alert was also issued for a two-year-old boy in Elton Bailey, Nashville. He was later found safe. Overall, the Amber Alerts issued this weekend resulted in the safe recovery of all the children involved.

name: Montenegro
summary: Multiple sources report a mass shooting in Montenegro that has resulted in multiple fatalities. The incident occurred in Cetinje, where an armed individual opened fire, killing at least 10 people, including two children. The suspect subsequently died from self-inflicted injuries. Officials have not yet released the motive for the shooting, but an investigation is underway. In a separate news article, the extradition of cryptocurrency mogul Do Kwon from Montenegro to the United States is reported in relation to the collapse of the TerraUSD cryptocurrency.

name: Miami Heat
summary: Pat Riley, the president of the Miami Heat, has dismissed rumors that All-Star Jimmy Butler will be traded, stating that the team is not considering such a move. Butler, however, has been noncommittal about his future with the Heat, saying that he is unsure if he wants to stay with the team. The Heat have been climbing in recent power rankings and will face the New Orleans Pelicans soon. Despite their success, the team has been the subject of a dig from the Houston Rockets' coach, who criticized Tyler Herro. The Heat have also signed Isaiah Stevens to a two-way contract and are preparing to face the Orlando Magic in an upcoming game.

name: Dan Lanning
summary: In anticipation of the Rose Bowl College Football Playoff match between Oregon and Ohio State, head coaches Dan Lanning and Ryan Day expressed their thoughts. Lanning acknowledged Oregon's shortcomings after their loss to Ohio State, but lauded 19-year-old Jeremiah Smith as "NFL ready." Both coaches commented on the ongoing lawsuit against Leonard Hamilton regarding NIL promises. Lanning also discussed the possibility of an "untouchable" record for Oregon and his views on the College Football Playoff format. Despite pressure to secure a Rose Bowl victory, Lanning's post-game remarks were met with criticism, while Day and Lanning both expressed excitement for the upcoming CFP battle.

name: Suns
summary: In a heated NBA matchup between the Phoenix Suns and Dallas Mavericks, three players were suspended for their involvement in an altercation. Suns player Cameron Payne threw a punch that led to the ejection of both him and Mavericks center Christian Wood. Additionally, Jae Crowder of the Suns was ejected. In related news, the Suns are reportedly exploring trade possibilities for Jusuf Nurkic. Following a loss to the Memphis Grizzlies, the Suns have listed Devin Booker as questionable for an upcoming game, while Ja Morant of the Grizzlies will be out.
